                            <p>There are lots of ways you can promote the census if you’re involved in your community.</p>

                            <p>You could:</p>

                            <ul>
                                <li>start talking about the census with your friends and family</li>
                                <li>tell people in your community about the census, its benefits and importance to them</li>
                                <li>raise awareness of the census in community organisations and any places people go to for advice</li>
                                <li>promote the census in things like community newsletters, meetings and social media groups</li>
                                <li>arrange for information to be added to a community website</li>
                                <li>offer the use of community spaces for census events</li>
                                <li>run a presentation to members of your community</li>
                            </ul>

                            <p>If you need help to promote the census, visit our <a href="{{pageInfo.rootPath}}/get-involved/downloadable-resources/">Downloadable resources</a> page. Here, we’ll provide resources that you can use in your community. There’ll be a range of materials from leaflets and posters to content for newsletters and social media posts.</p>

